HEADWORD: Ptyalism
<hw>Pty"a*lism</hw> <pr>(t⟦imac⟧"⟦adot⟧*l⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>ptyalismo`s</grk>, fr. <grk>ptyali`zein</grk> to spit
much, fr. <grk>pty`alon</grk> spittle, fr. <grk>pty`ein</grk> to spit:
cf. F. <ets>ptyalisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>Salivation, or an excessive
flow of saliva.</def> <rj><au>Quain.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
